				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Level 30 looking to fix up gear<a name="45989"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 14 04 6:28 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Also, switch your whip and the Di'Zok Wristsnapper, your offhand only attacks when you get a duel wield &quot;proc&quot; so having a higher damage primary will net you more dps since both weapons have the same delay.
<br />

<br />
Drop the batfang headband, they actually sell pretty well (1k obo on Rodcet) since it has EE2, and there are a lot of cheap helms that are much better and under 1k.  Easiest to get are probably the Crown of the Forlorn, Massive Flameguard Helm, and Foreman's Skullcap.
<br />

<br />
Easy boots that are fairly cheap would be Cotiere General's Boots, really less than 100pp and not too bad especially for a level 30.  Also, Lodizal Shell Boots are pretty nice, but for some reason they seem to be getting more expensive (at least on Rodcet).
<br />

<br />
Depending on how you play, a fairly good way to go about getting new gear is sorting by Bard/Race, Stat: HP, and going down the list to see the best thing you can afford.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Feydrioron of Rodcet Nife</span></td>
